%main.intro
  %h1 Local vs. Global
  %p.description
    When developing scenarios for small regions, it's easy to forget that your
    scenario is not an island, but affects &ndash; and is affected by &ndash;
    nearby regions. By combining the results for these areas, you can see how
    each individual contibutes to the whole.

  - if current_user
    - if current_user.saved_scenarios.count.zero?
      %p.description
        %strong
          You don't have any saved scenarios.
      %ol.description
        %li
          Start by creating a new scenario from
          %a(href=root_path) the home page
          %span> .
        %li
          Make your desired changes and save the scenario through the
          "settings" menu:
          %span#settings-menu-example
            Settings &rarr; Save scenario.
          #settings-menu-image
            = image_tag "pages/compare/settings-menu.#{I18n.locale}.png"
        %li
          Repeat until you have created all the scenarios you wish to compare
          and revisit this page.

    - else
      %p.description
        %strong
          Select two or more scenarios below to see how they compare&hellip;

      = form_tag compare_scenarios_path, method: 'get', class: 'select-scenarios' do
        %ul#available-scenarios
          = render partial: 'scenarios_slice', locals: { scenarios: @scenarios }
        #commit
          = submit_tag "#{t('scenario.local_vs_global')} â†’", name: 'combine'
  - else
    %p.description
      %strong
        You need to be
        = link_to 'logged in', login_path
        to compare scenarios.
